\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to define the complete lifecycle of work order management within the Elko County Information Operations Department,
 from initial intake through authorized closure.
 This policy establishes the work order as the non-negotiable unit of accountability for all IT work,
 regardless of origin,
 and defines the mandatory requirements for intake routing,
 triage,
 authorization,
 execution,
 documentation,
 and closure across all categories of IT activity.
 It further codifies the labor ceiling framework for Deprecated assets referenced in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

