\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Deprecated Asset Labor Ceiling
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Department operates on the principle that unreliable tools are replaced rather than indefinitely maintained.
 For Deprecated assets —
 those already formally identified for replacement —
 this principle governs remediation decisions.
 The Department's obligation is to keep the user functional for the duration of the replacement window,
 not to restore a failing asset to full health.
 Where an asset demonstrates a pattern of failure that undermines that reliability,
 the appropriate response is to accelerate replacement,
 not to continue investing remediation labor.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This framework operates through one objective trigger and a technician judgment pathway.
 Either activates the IT Director disposition review process.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Objective Trigger —
 Incident Frequency
\series default
:
 A Deprecated asset shall be flagged for IT Director disposition review when it generates five (5) or more reactive work orders within the same category within any rolling ninety (90) calendar day window.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The same-category requirement is essential.
 Five or more reactive tickets across different categories may indicate a heavily utilized asset.
 Five or more within the same category indicates a specific,
 repeating failure pattern in that functional dimension.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Tickets in different categories do not aggregate toward this trigger,
 even if the total exceeds five.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
For purposes of this trigger,
 reactive work orders are those submitted in response to asset failures or degradation,
 as distinct from IT-initiated maintenance or proactive work orders.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Technician Judgment Pathway
\series default
:
 The assigned technician may initiate a disposition review for any Deprecated asset at any time,
 independent of whether the objective trigger has been crossed.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The technician shall enter a written technical assessment in the work order record identifying the specific observations,
 failure patterns,
 or reliability concerns supporting the recommendation.
 Qualitative characterizations without supporting observations do not satisfy this requirement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
This pathway is the primary mechanism of this framework.
 Reliability failure does not always express itself in countable tickets —
 it expresses itself in whether the asset can be depended upon.
 That judgment,
 when documented,
 is sufficient basis for a disposition review.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall issue a written disposition decision within five (5) business days of the assessment being entered in the work order record.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director Disposition Review
\series default
:
 When a Deprecated asset is flagged under either mechanism,
 the Assistant IT Director shall notify the IT Director within one (1) business day,
 with a summary of the trigger conditions or technician assessment and the relevant work order history.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall issue a written disposition decision within five (5) business days of notification,
 except where the Technician Judgment Pathway specifies its own review window above.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The disposition decision shall be one of the following:
 (a) authorize replacement acceleration;
 (b) authorize continued remediation beyond the standard labor ceiling in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.2,
 with documented rationale;
 or (c) determine that the existing replacement timeline remains appropriate and direct that remediation continue within existing parameters.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All disposition decisions shall be documented in the relevant work order and in the IT Asset Catalog entry for the asset.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Proximity-to-Deadline Standard
\series default
:
 Deprecated assets with an established replacement deadline within thirty (30) calendar days of the date of triage shall be subject to a restricted remediation standard.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Remediation shall be limited to maintaining basic operational capability sufficient for the user to perform their assigned job function.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Full trigger framework analysis is not required for assets already imminently scheduled for replacement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The assigned technician shall inform the user of the replacement timeline and advise of any available interim workarounds.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exclusions from Disposition Decisions
\series default
:
 The following factors are explicitly excluded from consideration in any disposition decision made under this framework.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Sunk cost
\series default
:
 Prior investment in consumables,
 supplies,
 parts,
 or remediation labor is not a factor.
 Disposition shall be evaluated on the basis of forward-looking operational analysis only.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
End-user workflow disruption and preference
\series default
:
 If the user can perform their assigned job function,
 the operational standard is met.
 User preferences regarding specific equipment shall not influence IT disposition decisions.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
