\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 Emergency Exception
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
When an operational emergency requires immediate IT action before a work order can be created,
 the assigned technician or responding IT staff member may proceed with emergency action prior to work order creation.
 This exception is narrow.
 It applies only when the time required to create a work order before acting would materially extend the duration or severity of the impact.
 It does not represent a general relaxation of the work order requirement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The emergency exception suspends the sequence;
 it does not eliminate the requirement.
 A work order shall be created as soon as operationally practicable and in all cases no later than one (1) business hour following the initiation of emergency action or the conclusion of the immediate emergency phase,
 whichever is earlier.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Work orders created under this exception shall document:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The nature of the emergency and the specific conditions that justified bypassing standard work order creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All actions taken prior to work order creation,
 with the most precise timestamps recoverable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A notation in the work order that the emergency exception was invoked.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The acknowledgment of the Assistant IT Director,
 which shall occur within one (1) business day of work order creation.
\end_layout

